  "prompt": "What did George Lucas think of the Force Awakens?",
  "response": "George Lucas expressed mixed feelings about \"Star Wars: The Force Awakens.\" While he appreciated that the film introduced a new generation to the Star Wars universe and praised its visual effects and production quality, he was also critical of the story direction. Lucas felt that the film relied heavily on nostalgia and the established elements of the original trilogy instead of exploring new ideas and concepts. He had mentioned that he had his own vision for continuing the Star Wars saga, which was not used in the sequel trilogy. Overall, while he acknowledged the film's accomplishments, he wasn't entirely satisfied with its adherence to the original trilogy's themes and narrative style.",
